---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import DiscussCTA from '../components/DiscussCTA.astro';

const webpageSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  '@id': 'https://www.chandrakanojia.com/enterprise-ai-transformation/#webpage',
  url: 'https://www.chandrakanojia.com/enterprise-ai-transformation',
  name: 'Enterprise AI Execution in Regulated Enterprises | Chandra Kanojia',
  description: 'A practical point of view on enterprise AI, data readiness, CRM, workflow, controls, evidence, and regulated operating change.',
  isPartOf: { '@id': 'https://www.chandrakanojia.com/#website' },
  about: { '@id': 'https://www.chandrakanojia.com/#person' }
};

const breadcrumbSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
  itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://www.chandrakanojia.com' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Enterprise AI', item: 'https://www.chandrakanojia.com/enterprise-ai-transformation' }
  ]
};
---
<PageLayout
  title="Enterprise AI Execution in Regulated Enterprises | Chandra Kanojia"
  description="A practical point of view on enterprise AI, data readiness, CRM, workflow, controls, evidence, and regulated operating change."
  canonical="https://www.chandrakanojia.com/enterprise-ai-transformation"
  ogImage="/images/og-enterprise-ai.png"
  jsonLd={[webpageSchema, breadcrumbSchema]}
>
  <section class="page-hero" aria-labelledby="ai-title">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="kicker">Enterprise AI Point of View</p>
      <h1 id="ai-title">AI is moving faster than the enterprise.</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        The serious work starts after the assistant. Large organizations are learning that better tools do not automatically change how work gets done.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="shift-title">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="kicker">The shift</p>
      <h2 id="shift-title">The question is no longer whether AI can help. The question is whether the enterprise is ready for AI to touch the work.</h2>
      <p class="body-large" style="margin-top:1rem;">
        AI becomes useful when it lands inside the systems where work actually moves: CRM, case management, analytics, service platforms, approvals, controls, data handoffs, and leadership routines.
      </p>
      <p class="body-large" style="margin-top:1rem;">
        The model may be capable. The enterprise still has to decide which data can be trusted, which action is allowed, where the human returns, and how the outcome will be measured.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt" aria-labelledby="data-title">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="board-memo">
        <p class="kicker">The data reality</p>
        <h2 id="data-title">The data lake is not the decision point.</h2>
        <p class="body-large" style="margin-top:1rem;">
          The problem is rarely that data does not exist. The problem is that the right data is not trusted at the moment the work needs to move.
        </p>
        <p class="body-large" style="margin-top:1rem;">
          AI needs context the enterprise is willing to stand behind: source, freshness, ownership, lineage, evidence, and permission to use it in the workflow.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="principles-title">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading compact-heading">
        <p class="kicker">Operating truths</p>
        <h2 id="principles-title">What survives beyond the demo.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="principles">
        <article class="principle"><p>Work has to change before AI matters.</p></article>
        <article class="principle"><p>Data has to be trusted before AI can act.</p></article>
        <article class="principle"><p>Autonomy needs boundaries.</p></article>
        <article class="principle"><p>The test is not the demo. The test is cycle time, capacity, experience, risk, and value.</p></article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt" aria-labelledby="board-title">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="board-memo">
        <p class="kicker">The board question</p>
        <h2 id="board-title">Can management change the work without weakening trust?</h2>
        <p class="body-large" style="margin-top:1rem;">
          Leaders do not need another impressive demo. They need to know what evidence the AI used, what data it can trust, what it is allowed to do, when a human returns, how the action is logged, and whether the result improved the business.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <DiscussCTA
    id="ai-cta"
    eyebrow="Discuss the mandate"
    title="The useful conversation starts where AI meets real work."
    body="Talk to Chandra about trusted data, CRM/Salesforce, workflow, controlled action, adoption, platform reliability, and risk-aware operating change."
  />
</PageLayout>
